Biography

2022: Played in 17 games, earning one start...Lone start came against ETSU (9/8)...Played a season-high 37 minutes one game later at College of Charleston (9/11).

Graduate transfer from Bucknell University (2018-2021)...Played in 61 career games and won the Patriot League Title in 2021...Academically member of the Patriot League Academic Honor Roll all four years.

2021: Finished off her Bucknell career with a Patriot League championship ... appeared in 20 games off the bench, with a high of 33 minutes against American ... Finished the season with four shots and two shots on goal.

2020-21: Played in four games off the bench in the abbreviated spring 2021 season, totaling 59 minutes ... attempted two shots.

2019: Played in all 18 matches as a reserve forward ... recorded one goal and one assist ... scored the lone goal in a 1-0 win over Boston University ... named Patriot League Offensive Player of the Week after that contest ... played a season-high 54 minutes against Pittsburgh.

2018: Played in all 19 games with 13 starts ... started the final 11 games of the season ... finished with one goal and one assist, and attempted 12 shots ... scored in her second career appearance, a 4-1 win over Niagara ... played the full game four times, including all 110 minutes against Lehigh in the Patriot League Tournament quarterfinals.

High School: Played at Battlefield High School, where she finished her career with 84 goals, second-most in program history, and 27 assists...Team was ranked No. 1 in the nation by USA Today in 2017...As senior was named 1st team All-Region, 1st Team All-Conference, 2nd Team All-State, and 2nd Team All-Met...Was also the team captain and team MVP her senior year...Also collected All-Conference and All-Region honors as a freshman, sophomore, and junior...Played club for FC Virginia winning NPL National Championship...Also won Mid-Atlantic Conference Championship in 2015 and 2016, USYS Region 1 Championship, and Virginia State Cup Championship.

Personal: Born on October 10, 1999...daughter of John and Laurel Parham...Has an older brother, Haydon, and a younger brother, Colton...Grandfather Randall Haydon played tennis for UMass Amherst...Enjoys snowboarding, hiking, and reading.
